quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  15,1,"Alif, Lam, Ra. These are verses of the Book, the Qur'an which makes things clear."
  15,2,"On occasions, the disbelievers would wish that they were Muslims."
  15,3,"Let them eat and enjoy, and let (their) fancy make them neglectful, for they shall soon come to know."
  15,4,"And We did not destroy any town, but it had a pre-determined decree."
  15,5,"No people can precede their appointed time nor can they exceed it."
  15,6,"And they said, "0 you to whom the Dhikr (the Qur'an) has been revealed, you are certainly insane."
  15,7,"Why do you not bring the angels to us if you are among the truthful?""
  15,8,"We do not send down the angels except with what is true and then they shall be given no res-pite."
  15,9,"We, Ourselves, have sent down the Dhikr (the Qur'an), and We are there to protect it."
  15,10,"And We did send the messengers before you among the groups of earlier peoples."
  15,11,"And no messenger came to them but they used to mock at him."
  15,12,"This is how We make it enter into the hearts of the sinners,"
  15,13,"(where-by) they do not believe in it (the Qu’ an). And this has been the way of earlier people."
  15,14,"And even if We were to open a gate in the sky and they keep ascending through it,"
  15,15,"still they will say, 'It is nothing but that our eyes have been deluded and that we are a people bewitched."